<!DOCTYPE html>

<html lang="en" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
<head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <title>Otava</title>
    <link href="../style/style.css" rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" />
</head>
<body>
    <h1>Otava</h1>

    <p>
        Otava is an experimental C++ compiler whose scanners and parsers are generated using <span class="mono">Soul</span>.
        It generates x64 assembly code and uses <span class="mono">msbuild</span> to compile the assembly files to object code,
        to archive object files in libraries, to compile main C++ files of programs and to link programs.
    </p>
    
    <p>
        Before we can compile C++ programs with Otava, its standard library <span class="mono">std</span> must be compiled for each configuration used:
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li>
            Please complete the <span class="mono"><a href="../installation/installation.html">installation</a></span> steps if you have not done so yet.
        </li>
        <li>
            Start a terminal in the <span class="mono">C:\soul-5.0.0\tools\otava\std</span> directory
            and enter command <span class="mono">oc std.project</span>:
            <div class="console">
